A peanut which is uniform in size and is from a runner peanut cultivar.

The uniform size of runner peanuts enable even roasting and so is attractive for making peanut butter. It is typically grown in the states of Georgia, Texas, Alabama, Florida, South Carolina and Oklahoma; and accounts for 80 percent of the peanuts grown in the United States. [https://www.nationalpeanutboard.org/peanut-info/peanut-types.htm]
